the little mermaid was my favorite Disney movie, wbu?

It is the second time this month that the ocean brings me to tears. Yes tears. Like crying, balling like a baby. Idk if it’s happiness, sadness, overt joy. I don’t know.

The first time was when I was snorkeling the reefs in Hawaii. The beauty. The colors. The reefs. The fish. I couldn’t believe I was so blessed to witness the beauty up close and personal. It was an honor, a privilege, it was unforgettable.
The second time I balled my eyes out was last night watching “Avatar: the way of water”. Like literally there was a point where tears were going down my face uncontrollably. Just waterworks coming from my eyes. 
I was for sure releasing or something.
I left the movie feeling so different about the ocean i know and love. Loving it 10000xs more than I already do. But loving it in a different way..
If you love something there’s no better feeling than sharing it, and all i want is to someday take our kids and our kids kids and our kids kids kids to see the beauty of the reefs and wildlife I’ve had the privilege of seeing in my life. But that’s not gonna happen if WE don’t start taking care of this planet.
Im still learning and I’m currently doing my research on how to be more involved, but all i want is to start making efforts towards conserving the ocean.
We have to prevent the human effects on it as much as we possibly can.
It’s not just take take take.
We have to take CARE of the planet we live on. 
Over 50% of the worlds reefs have died over the last 30 years. And by 2050 90% of our reefs will be gone…
I remember when i was 8 years old going all over the Florida keys seeing the most breathtakingly colorful coral and now most of it is gone due to bleaching and climate change effects. I witnessed it myself in Hawaii. The bit of reefs that we saw werent as vibrant as i remember them being when I was younger in the keys. Nonetheless they were still stunning and the biggest highlight of my trip BUT STILL. We can’t continue to ignore the facts and the signs of deterioration.
“If you love a flower, don’t pick it up…”🦋
Love y’all and i hope you can see this and make your own strides as well. We are the change.

iiiiiiii I feel so good 💌💌💌

Btw this class format was one of my favorites of the year. So intimate and with the intimacy I was able to get creative. i normally always perform alone in the end of class, and groups of my students go together in groups of 5 before me. But this was nice cause I had time to think and decide what I wanted to do with nobody rushing me out of the room in the end. So I decided to do it backwards. To challenge my students, they almost all performed ALONE.
And I went with them all in the end (this vid hehe) 
why does that feel so much more right?!?
I do love the idea of performing your own choreo in the end but it’s always such an awkward spotlight moment and honestly makes me cringe sometimes lol (for myself haha) 
I felt so much more right feeling united with my students in the end rather than just doing it alone, u know?

def doing this more in 20233333

One of the most calming and soothing experiences of 2022: swimming with sharks in Hawaii.
We were surrounded by probably 25 sharks in the open ocean. And lemme tell you, I WAS SCARED. Before we got in I was for sure panicking, but once we were in the water I realized how beautiful and calm these creatures actually are.
They don’t wanna hurt us. Most of the time when they do, it is from mis-interpretation or murky waters.
I can’t express enough how shook I was by my changed perspective on sharks.
I love them now.
And it sucks that media makes us believe they are these horrible creatures when they’re literally so kind and sweet and curious.
Of course some of them are more aggressive than others. These were Galapagos!🥺

Thank you @danny_mako and @hawaiiadventurediving for sharing this experience with us🙏🏽🙏🏽🙏🏽
Best day ever. Forever changed.

And thank you for these PICTURES…. @danny_mako Wow wow wow🦋 a true artist, please go follow him for more content like this! I remember when he reached out to Pam while we were in Hawaii to go shark diving. We saw his page and I was like oh that’s def photoshopped, no way!! First of all i couldn’t believe anybody would ever swim with wild sharks like that. And second of all the pictures were so epic I was in disbelief it was even real. 📸🤍

P.S.- if you’re going to do something like this please do it with professionals who know what they are doing, i highly recommend @hawaiiadventurediving :)

27 and lookin like heaven 🌞

Thank you guys for the outpour of love on my birthday. I love you guys so so so much and I wish for you a prosperous, grateful, and healthy new year.

I thought every year that passed I wouldn’t care about age. And I kinda don’t but I kinda do this year…🥹

But i know that age is a mindset, and the way you feel is the way you look, and I feeel gewwwwwd🥲
On the inside I feel strong, loving, more egoless every day. Wiser, savvy, and less immature lol.
I love the woman I am and am becoming every day.
And something I do love about the years is that they give me the courage and the fearlessness to go after my dreams. They give you an idgaf attitude. And there’s nothing better than not taking life so seriously.

This year will be the year of going after everything I’ve pushed to the side my whole life due to fear…
I feel this year coming is gonna be unexpected, beautiful, everything I ever dreamed of and more. Just gotta keep putting in the work and the fruits of my labor will pay off.

Love you alllll

Hehehehe 7 years and counting.. the blessings🙏🏽🙏🏽

I love my @bangenergy family. Many and most of you know my story. But if you don’t:

Bang was the first company to ever reach out to me when I had 16,000 followers on instagram. They believed in me before half the world did. They believed in my energy before I had any skill. And they took my family and I out of what felt like a never-ending financial struggle of 7 years.

I grew up financially comfortable. My parents always gave us everything we needed and wanted. They worked their asses off to give us a beautiful life!
We had nice things; a boat, a nice house on the water in Florida, we went on trips down to the keys more times than I can remember, weekends were always spent on our boat soaking up the sun with our family and friends…
But when the recession hit my parents lost their company, their store, our cars, our house, our properties, even their legal documentation in this country, literally everything. 
We kinda hit rock bottom. 
We lost everything material i guess you can say.
But we never lost the love, or the creativity, or our artistry.

When I started shuffling and got signed by bang we finally started to see a life like the one we once had.
We started to feel financial freedom again. And for THAT i will be endlessly grateful till the day I die.

Money doesn’t buy happiness and I know that because I’ve had it all and I’ve lost it all. But it sure is nice to have the means to see the beautiful planet we live on, and to see the people you love not living in stress or angst.

Your life is filled with endless possibilities. You can live off of your art especially in times like today with the beauty of social media. Don’t ever settle for what life throws at you. Especially if it’s not fulfilling your soul. 
You just have to believe in yourself AS CLICHE AS THAT MAY SOUND. And put in the work to be the best version of you you can be.

Count your blessings 🫶🏽🦋🫶🏽
So grateful for yall 
Ok love u bye

Electric Daisy Carnival 2023 — one for the books 🦋

Omg guys i didn’t even tell you about my foot!!!
Okay so the day i arrived at @edc_lasvegas (Wednesday) to set up our RV and our vendor shop, at night i went to go open my pull out bed in the RV and dropped the whole metal bed on my right big toe…… 
I thought my weekend was over before it had even started. I was bleeding and their was a gash going across my toe. It was horrrrrrid.
Like honestly I could’ve made it out to be the worst thing ever and victimized myself but instead i iced it, put some triple antibiotic on it and tried to ignore that anything had happened. Even though i was totally limping and def had pain in that moment.
Friday came and by the grace of god, I felt no pain and literally forgot that anything had even occurred. Especially during my class, adrenaline took over and i even wore sneakers with no pain in my class.
I healed so quick and I’m so grateful for these strong ass limbs i have. 
Your mind is so powerful. The moment you put energy towards something it becomes bigger and bigger. If you ignore the drama, you can literally make a giant open gash in your foot feel like nothing😂
Kinda crazy.
Where focus goes - energy flows, i had way bigger blessings to focus on this weekend. Only time i even remembered was when I’d come home to sleep and look down and notice i still had a giant open cut🤣

THE MIND IS CRAZY. I could go on forever about how powerful it is but that’s all I’ll share.

Love y’all and thank you to everyone who shared a moment on that dance floor with me this past week! 
You guys are amazing🦋🦋🦋

Can you believe it’s been 3 years since quarantine? 
Unpopular opinion but sometimes I miss it. Obviously not the loss, or the pain it brought to so many, but there is always a silver lining in life. And there are some things i do miss about those times…
The simplicity and pause of the world. 
The slower times. 
Everyone just stuck at home trying new things.
I loved the togetherness of it all.
The thought that everyone was in it together was comforting. I never had fomo, lol.
It’s like we felt a little more connected with each other oddly, even though we were isolated.
We were forced to look within, about so many parts of our lives, with all that time we had on our hands. 
You really got to know yourself. The people around you.
The truth about a lot of things.
Veils we’re uncovered.
Fighting for justice.
What a year.

2020 was transformative.

Obviously there was a lot of toughness that came with it. Loss, mainly, of all sorts. And if you had to say goodbye to anyone or anything because of it, I hope you got through it and came out stronger and wiser, 
& you know what.. I KNOW you did!!
I hope that whatever you had to undergo within the last three years has shaped you in marvelous ways. 
I hope you are thriving, and if you’re not i promise your time is coming 🙏🏽🧚🏼‍♀️✨ 

But foreal, I just don’t understand where tf the time has gone!!!
I swear we blinked and three years just flew by. You can’t take moments and time for granted.
TIME is such a precious thing. 
Use it wiselyyyy. stop wasting it on anything that steals your YOU.
If you’re feeling lost atm,
here’s my current life advice (to myself and to you):
Drop the BS, stop looking around you to find fulfillment, and figure out who ✨YOU✨ are, at your core, let that be the guide to whatever it is you do with your life.
No one is you and that is your power🦋, 
Dont let life pass you by without making that dream of yours a reality. 

You’ll never have this exact version of you back. 
Be with yourself. 
Just be.

I love you guyyyys.
Always wishing you guys so much happiness and peace.

P.s.- not trying to sound insensitive here all my love and gratitude goes to the frontline workers during that time🙏🏽🙏🏽🙏🏽

Crazy to think this is my last @bangenergy shuffle video…
Thank you to Bang Energy for being my support and backbone for the past 6 and a half years. 
For showing me the world. Taking me out of the country for the first time. Giving me the first feeling of financial abundance and security in my entire life. 
And most importantly, giving me and my family peace in one of the hardest financial struggles we’d ever gone through.

At the age of 21, when i had 15,000 followers i got my first brand deal email, and it was with Bang, i thought i was dreaming… getting paid to post my passion?! A DREAM COME TRUE.
 
They believed in shufflers when no company did.
 
I would not be where I am today without Bang.
And quite frankly i don’t even know what it’s like to be an influencer without it… (embarrassingly lol)
It’s kinda crazy I’ve been with them as long as I’ve been shuffling and as long as I’ve been posting on social media.
We grew together.
 
letting go is harder than I ever thought
The memories keep me up at night
It’s the end of an era,
& it’s so bittersweet
But I’m excited to fly on my own
I’m so confident the best is yet to come.
 
Thank you for literally everything🙏🏽 I’ll never be able repay you

Tokyooooo, i miss you. I miss the calmness. I miss the vibrant yet gray color grade. I miss not understanding anything i read. I miss the lack of trash cans. I miss the quiet train rides. The inspiring fashion anywhere you look. The anime on even serious things. The cat cafes. The self sufficient 5yr olds. The music. The maids. The onigiri. 7/11s. Harajuku. Fruit sandos. The schoolgirls. Skirts. The wholesome interactions. —The SUSSSHIIIIIIII🥵😫🤤

What a trip. Literally a trippy and beautiful and safe city. 
I felt like i was in a black mirror episode the whole time.
I can def see myself living there someday. Even just for a month.
To travel is to expand.
To embrace a different way of living can only lead to growth and better understanding of the world around you.
Feeling beyond blessed for the journey we just had traveling through Asia.
And of course feeling emo, when am i not?
So here’s a lil freestyle to my fave emo song right now, shot in the anime district of Tokyo called Akihabara!
